The paper discusses the development of a simulator for autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of machine intelligence and deep learning also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The simulator's ability to operate in real-time and support hardware-in-the-loop simulations relates to systems and control (cs.SY). The use of visually realistic simulations suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV), and the mention of modular design and component reusability suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
